	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Savannah</placeName> <date>March 19. 1839</date>.</p>
				<p>My dear Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">The arrival of the Schooner Heroine yes&#61;<lb/>terday brought me your esteemed favour of the <date>1st</date> instant and<lb/> also the five copies of your work&#44; which I shall deliver tomorrow<lb/> to those who subscribed for them&#44; and remit you the amount<lb/> as soon as received&#59; the only difficulty I shall have will be as to the<lb/> manner of making the remittance&#44; as I could not procure a<lb/> draft on your City for so small an amount&#44; however should<lb/> I not be able to do so&#44; will send it by <persName>Doctor De LaMotta</persName><lb/> who writes me that he will leave <placeName>Charleston</placeName> for the <placeName>north</placeName> soon<lb/> after the <date>Passover</date> Holidays&#59;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Judging from the one or two discourses<lb/> of your collections that I have as yet read I am certain I shall be<lb/> <sic>be</sic> pleased with them they give an <add>&#63;</add> of what the others are<lb/> and <add>&#63;</add> us&#44; do much in diffusing a correct knowledge of<lb/> our Holy Religion&#8222; the <sic>exersions</sic> my dear Sir you have and are<lb/> still making for that purpose is creditable to yourself and<lb/> desires the support of all of us the children of <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#44; you<lb/> shall have mine and you will please consider me a standing<lb/> subscriber to all the works you are now or may hereafter pub<lb/>lish&#44; the mechanical part of the book is well done&#44; and I am<lb/> much pleased with the specimen you have not use of<lb/> your Book of Daily Prayers &#38;c be assured I shall use my <sic>exersions</sic><lb/> to get you as many subscribers as can be obtained in<lb/> our small community&#44; tho&#39; I cannot promise you to<lb/> get many as most of the few who are followers of the</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>religion of their Forefathers are already supplied.  I can however<lb/> promise you one thing and that is my best <sic>exersions</sic>.<lb/>  The weather here is delightfully fine&#44; tho&#39; on the <date>4th</date> just Instant<lb/> we witnessed here the novel sight of a Snow Storm which<lb/> lasted just sufficiently long to gratify those who had never<lb/> before enjoyed the pleasure of a <sic>Slay</sic> ride and Snow balling.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">With my best wishes for your success and sincerely recipro&#45;<lb/>&#61;cating your kind wishes  I remain Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Your friend &#38; well wisher</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">J. De La Motta Junr.</persName></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
